<h1>Warning</h1>
{% if public or unsourced %}
<p><strong>Your torrent has been uploaded; however, you must download your torrent from <a href="torrents.php?id={{ group_id }}">here</a> because:</strong></p>
<ul>
    {% if public %}
    <li><strong>You didn't make your torrent using the "private" option</strong></li>
    {% endif %}
    {% if unsourced %}
    <li><strong>The "source" flag was not set to OPS. Please read the <a href="/wiki.php?action=article&id={{ wiki_id }}">wiki page about source flags</a> to find out why this is important. </strong></li>
    {% endif %}
</ul>
{% endif %}
{% if clash > 1 %}
<p><strong class="important">You upload is complete, however, {{ clash }}
torrent{{ clash|plural }} has a folder name that clashes with another torrent
(which is either in this upload or already on site). This may cause problems if
people attempt to download both torrents in the same client.</strong></p>
<p>You might want to make a cup of tea and rethink your naming strategy. You can
remove the upload now, before people start queuing it up. You can then adjust
the folder name locally and try again.</p>
{% endif %}
